== 地区趋势和短期波动 ==
[[File:GISS_temperature_2000-09.png|320px]]
全球变暖指的是全球平均温度的增加，但并不是全球每个地方增幅一致，不同地区的差异是非常大的。<ref name="WarmingHole-SE-USA">{{cite news|last1=Leavenworth|first1=Stuart|title=Snow-covered beaches? Chilly iguanas? They are part of a mysterious ‘hole’ in global warming|url=https://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/national/article200169249.html|work=McClatchy Washington Bureau|date=2018-02-15|accessdate=2018-12-30|archive-date=2019-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203141631/https://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/national/article200169249.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>自从1979年以来，全球陆地平均温度的增幅是海洋的2倍(每10年增温0.25°C比0.13°C)。<ref>Trenberth ''et al.'', [http://archive.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/ch3.html Chap 3, Observations: Atmospheric Surface and Climate Change] {{Wayback|url=http://archive.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/ch3.html |date=20181223163923 }}, [http://archive.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/ch3s3-es.html Executive Summary] {{Wayback|url=http://archive.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/ch3s3-es.html |date=20181222223057 }}, [http://archive.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter3.pdf p. 237] {{Wayback|url=http://archive.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter3.pdf |date=20181223163844 }}, in {{Harvnb|IPCC AR4 WG1|2007}}.</ref>海洋温度比陆地增加的慢是因为其[[热容量|热容量]]更大，且可以通过[[蒸发|蒸发]]来散发更多的热量。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sutton|first=Rowan T.|last2=Dong|first2=Buwen|last3=Gregory|first3=Jonathan M.|title=Land/sea warming ratio in response to climate change: IPCC AR4 model results and comparison with observations|url=http://www.agu.org/pubs/crossref/2007/2006GL028164.shtml|journal=Geophysical Research Letters|publication-date=16 January 2007|volume=34|issue=2|page=L02701|bibcode=2007GeoRL..3402701S|doi=10.1029/2006GL028164|accessdate=2007-09-19|ref=harv|archive-date=2012-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923041910/http://www.agu.org/pubs/crossref/2007/2006GL028164.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>自从18世纪开始[[第一次工业革命|工业化]]以来，南北{{tsl|en|Hemispheres of Earth|半球}}的温度差异便增大了，因为北半球的雪和海冰的融化更多，并且陆地占比更大。<ref>{{cite journal|last=Feulner|first=Georg|author2=Rahmstorf, Stefan|author3=Levermann, Anders|author4=Volkwardt, Silvia|title=On the Origin of the Surface Air Temperature Difference Between the Hemispheres in Earth's Present-Day Climate|journal=Journal of Climate|date=March 2013|doi=10.1175/JCLI-D-12-00636.1|url=http://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/abs/10.1175/JCLI-D-12-00636.1|accessdate=2013-04-25|pages=130325101629005|ref=harv|volume=26|bibcode=2013JCli...26.7136F|archive-date=2015-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330093005/http://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/abs/10.1175/JCLI-D-12-00636.1|dead-url=no}}</ref>在过去的100年里，北极的平均温升幅度几乎是地球其它地区的2倍，<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://archive.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/tssts-3-1-2.html |title=TS.3.1.2 Spatial Distribution of Changes in Temperature, Circulation and Related Variables – AR4 WGI Technical Summary<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2018-12-30 |archive-date=2018-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181223121212/https://archive.ipcc.ch/publications_and_data/ar4/wg1/en/tssts-3-1-2.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>这种现象有时候被称为“{{tsl|en|Arctic amplification|北极放大}}”。

尽管北半球的温室气体排放比南半球多，但这并不是形成南北半球温差的原因，因为主要的温室气体在大气中存在的时间比其在全球范围内扩散均匀的时间要长很多。<ref>Ehhalt ''et al.'', [http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/127.htm Chapter 4: Atmospheric Chemistry and Greenhouse Gases], {{Wayback|url=http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/127.htm |date=20120123063256 }} [http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/139.htm#4231 Section 4.2.3.1: Carbon monoxide (CO) and hydrogen (H<sub>2</sub>)], {{Wayback|url=http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/139.htm#4231 |date=20120409122116 }} [http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/pdf/TAR-04.pdf p. 256], {{Wayback|url=http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/pdf/TAR-04.pdf |date=20120117054647 }} in {{Harvnb|IPCC TAR WG1|2001}}.</ref>

